33 // Setup for Windows DLL export/import. When building the V8 DLL the
34 // BUILDING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When building a program which uses
35 // the V8 DLL USING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When either building the V8
36 // static library or building a program which uses the V8 static library neither
37 // BUILDING_V8_SHARED nor USING_V8_SHARED should be defined.
38 #ifdef BUILDING_V8_SHARED
39 # define V8_EXPORT __declspec(dllexport)
40 #elif USING_V8_SHARED
41 # define V8_EXPORT __declspec(dllimport)
42 #else
43 # define V8_EXPORT
44 #endif // BUILDING_V8_SHARED
45 
46 #else // V8_OS_WIN
47 
48 // Setup for Linux shared library export.
49 #if V8_HAS_ATTRIBUTE_VISIBILITY
50 # ifdef BUILDING_V8_SHARED
51 # define V8_EXPORT __attribute__ ((visibility("default")))
52 # else
53 # define V8_EXPORT
54 # endif
55 #else
56 # define V8_EXPORT
57 #endif
58 
59 #endif // V8_OS_WIN

159 #define TYPE_CHECK(T, S) \
160  while (false) { \
161  *(static_cast<T* volatile*>(0)) = static_cast<S*>(0); \
162  }

195 template <class T>
196 class Local {
197  public:
198  V8_INLINE Local() : val_(0) {}
199  template <class S>
200  V8_INLINE Local(Local<S> that)
201  : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
207  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
208  }
209 
213  V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == 0; }
214 
218  V8_INLINE void Clear() { val_ = 0; }
219 
220  V8_INLINE T* operator->() const { return val_; }
221 
222  V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return val_; }
223 
230  template <class S>
231  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
232  internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
233  internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
234  if (a == 0) return b == 0;
235  if (b == 0) return false;
236  return *a == *b;
237  }
238 
239  template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator==(
240  const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
241  internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
242  internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
243  if (a == 0) return b == 0;
244  if (b == 0) return false;
245  return *a == *b;
246  }
247 
254  template <class S>
255  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
256  return !operator==(that);
257  }
258 
259  template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator!=(
260  const Persistent<S>& that) const {
261  return !operator==(that);
262  }

269  template <class S> V8_INLINE static Local<T> Cast(Local<S> that) {
270 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
271  // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
272  // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
273  if (that.IsEmpty()) return Local<T>();
274 #endif
275  return Local<T>(T::Cast(*that));
276  }
277 
283  template <class S>
284  V8_INLINE Local<S> As() const {
285  return Local<S>::Cast(*this);
286  }
287 
293  V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, Local<T> that);
294  V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
295  const PersistentBase<T>& that);
296 
297  private:
298  friend class Utils;
299  template<class F> friend class Eternal;
300  template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
301  template<class F, class M> friend class Persistent;
302  template<class F> friend class Local;
303  template <class F>
304  friend class MaybeLocal;
305  template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
306  template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
307  friend class String;
308  friend class Object;
309  friend class Context;
310  friend class Private;
311  template<class F> friend class internal::CustomArguments;
312  friend Local<Primitive> Undefined(Isolate* isolate);
313  friend Local<Primitive> Null(Isolate* isolate);
314  friend Local<Boolean> True(Isolate* isolate);
315  friend Local<Boolean> False(Isolate* isolate);
316  friend class HandleScope;
317  friend class EscapableHandleScope;
318  template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
319  friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
320  template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
321  template <class F>
322  friend class ReturnValue;
323 
324  explicit V8_INLINE Local(T* that) : val_(that) {}
325  V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
326  T* val_;
327 };

363  template <class S>
364  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool ToLocal(Local<S>* out) const {
365  out->val_ = IsEmpty() ? nullptr : this->val_;
366  return !IsEmpty();

409 static const int kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
410 static const int kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
411 
412 template <typename T>
413 class WeakCallbackInfo {
414  public:
415  typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
416 
417  WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
418  void* embedder_fields[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback],
419  Callback* callback)
420  : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
421  for (int i = 0; i < kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
422  embedder_fields_[i] = embedder_fields[i];
423  }
424  }
425 
426  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
427  V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
428  V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
429 
430  V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED("use indexed version",
431  void* GetInternalField1() const) {
432  return embedder_fields_[0];
433  }
434  V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED("use indexed version",
435  void* GetInternalField2() const) {
436  return embedder_fields_[1];
437  }
438 
439  V8_DEPRECATED("Not realiable once SetSecondPassCallback() was used.",
440  bool IsFirstPass() const) {
441  return callback_ != nullptr;
442  }
443 
444  // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
445  // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
446  // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
447  // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
448  // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
449  // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
450  void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
451 
452  private:
453  Isolate* isolate_;
454  T* parameter_;
455  Callback* callback_;
456  void* embedder_fields_[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback];
457 };
458 
459 
460 // kParameter will pass a void* parameter back to the callback, kInternalFields
461 // will pass the first two internal fields back to the callback, kFinalizer
462 // will pass a void* parameter back, but is invoked before the object is
463 // actually collected, so it can be resurrected. In the last case, it is not
464 // possible to request a second pass callback.
465 enum class WeakCallbackType { kParameter, kInternalFields, kFinalizer };
466

520  internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
521  if (a == NULL) return b == NULL;

635 template<class T>
636 class NonCopyablePersistentTraits {
637  public:
638  typedef Persistent<T, NonCopyablePersistentTraits<T> > NonCopyablePersistent;
639  static const bool kResetInDestructor = false;
640  template<class S, class M>
641  V8_INLINE static void Copy(const Persistent<S, M>& source,
642  NonCopyablePersistent* dest) {
643  Uncompilable<Object>();
644  }
645  // TODO(dcarney): come up with a good compile error here.
646  template<class O> V8_INLINE static void Uncompilable() {
647  TYPE_CHECK(O, Primitive);
648  }
649 };

676 template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
677  public:
681  V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(0) { }
687  template <class S>
688  V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
689  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
690  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
691  }
697  template <class S, class M2>
698  V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
699  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
700  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
701  }
708  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
709  Copy(that);
710  }
711  template <class S, class M2>
712  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
713  Copy(that);
714  }
715  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) { // NOLINT
716  Copy(that);
717  return *this;
718  }
719  template <class S, class M2>
720  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
721  Copy(that);
722  return *this;
723  }
729  V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
730  if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
731  }
732 
733  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
734  template <class S>
735  V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(const Persistent<S>& that) { // NOLINT
736 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
737  // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
738  // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
739  if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
740 #endif
741  return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(const_cast<Persistent<S>&>(that));
742  }
743 
744  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
745  template <class S>
746  V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() const { // NOLINT
747  return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
748  }
749 
750  private:
751  friend class Isolate;
752  friend class Utils;
753  template<class F> friend class Local;
754  template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
755  template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
756 
757  explicit V8_INLINE Persistent(T* that) : PersistentBase<T>(that) {}
758  V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
759  template<class S, class M2>
760  V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that);
761 };

769 template <class T>
770 class Global : public PersistentBase<T> {
771  public:
775  V8_INLINE Global() : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {}
781  template <class S>
782  V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
783  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
784  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
785  }
791  template <class S>
792  V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<S>& that)
793  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, that.val_)) {
794  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
795  }
799  V8_INLINE Global(Global&& other) : PersistentBase<T>(other.val_) { // NOLINT
800  other.val_ = nullptr;
801  }
802  V8_INLINE ~Global() { this->Reset(); }
806  template <class S>
807  V8_INLINE Global& operator=(Global<S>&& rhs) { // NOLINT
808  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
809  if (this != &rhs) {
810  this->Reset();
811  this->val_ = rhs.val_;
812  rhs.val_ = nullptr;
813  }
814  return *this;
815  }
819  Global Pass() { return static_cast<Global&&>(*this); } // NOLINT
820 
821  /*
822  * For compatibility with Chromium's base::Bind (base::Passed).
823  */
824  typedef void MoveOnlyTypeForCPP03;
825 
826  Global(const Global&) = delete;
827  void operator=(const Global&) = delete;
828 
829  private:
830  template <class F>
831  friend class ReturnValue;
832  V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
833 };

855 class V8_EXPORT HandleScope {

877 
878  static internal::Object** CreateHandle(internal::Isolate* isolate,
879  internal::Object* value);
880 
881  private:
882  // Declaring operator new and delete as deleted is not spec compliant.
883  // Therefore declare them private instead to disable dynamic alloc
884  void* operator new(size_t size);
885  void* operator new[](size_t size);
886  void operator delete(void*, size_t);
887  void operator delete[](void*, size_t);

898  template<class F> friend class Local;
899 
900  // Object::GetInternalField and Context::GetEmbedderData use CreateHandle with
901  // a HeapObject* in their shortcuts.
902  friend class Object;

904 };

987  bool is_opaque = false, bool is_wasm = false,
988  bool is_module = false)
989  : flags_((is_shared_cross_origin ? kIsSharedCrossOrigin : 0) |
990  (is_wasm ? kIsWasm : 0) | (is_opaque ? kIsOpaque : 0) |
991  (is_module ? kIsModule : 0)) {}
992  V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(int flags)
993  : flags_(flags &
994  (kIsSharedCrossOrigin | kIsOpaque | kIsWasm | kIsModule)) {}
995 
996  bool IsSharedCrossOrigin() const {
997  return (flags_ & kIsSharedCrossOrigin) != 0;
998  }
999  bool IsOpaque() const { return (flags_ & kIsOpaque) != 0; }
1000  bool IsWasm() const { return (flags_ & kIsWasm) != 0; }
1001  bool IsModule() const { return (flags_ & kIsModule) != 0; }
1002 
1003  int Flags() const { return flags_; }
1004 
1005  private:
1006  enum {
1007  kIsSharedCrossOrigin = 1,
1008  kIsOpaque = 1 << 1,
1009  kIsWasm = 1 << 2,
1010  kIsModule = 1 << 3
1011  };
1012  const int flags_;
1013 };

1217 class V8_EXPORT ScriptCompiler {
1218  public:
1226  struct V8_EXPORT CachedData {
1227  enum BufferPolicy {
1228  BufferNotOwned,
1229  BufferOwned
1230  };
1231 
1232  CachedData()
1233  : data(NULL),
1234  length(0),
1235  rejected(false),
1236  buffer_policy(BufferNotOwned) {}
1237 
1238  // If buffer_policy is BufferNotOwned, the caller keeps the ownership of
1239  // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is
1240  // destroyed. If the policy is BufferOwned, the given data will be deleted
1241  // (with delete[]) when the CachedData object is destroyed.
1242  CachedData(const uint8_t* data, int length,
1243  BufferPolicy buffer_policy = BufferNotOwned);
1244  ~CachedData();
1245  // TODO(marja): Async compilation; add constructors which take a callback
1246  // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.
1247  const uint8_t* data;
1248  int length;
1249  bool rejected;
1250  BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
1251 
1252  // Prevent copying.
1253  CachedData(const CachedData&) = delete;
1254  CachedData& operator=(const CachedData&) = delete;
1255  };
1256 
1260  class Source {
1261  public:
1262  // Source takes ownership of CachedData.
1263  V8_INLINE Source(Local<String> source_string, const ScriptOrigin& origin,
1264  CachedData* cached_data = NULL);
1265  V8_INLINE Source(Local<String> source_string,
1266  CachedData* cached_data = NULL);
1267  V8_INLINE ~Source();
1268 
1269  // Ownership of the CachedData or its buffers is *not* transferred to the
1270  // caller. The CachedData object is alive as long as the Source object is
1271  // alive.
1272  V8_INLINE const CachedData* GetCachedData() const;
1273 
1274  V8_INLINE const ScriptOriginOptions& GetResourceOptions() const;
1275 
1276  // Prevent copying.
1277  Source(const Source&) = delete;
1278  Source& operator=(const Source&) = delete;
1279 
1280  private:
1281  friend class ScriptCompiler;
1282 
1283  Local<String> source_string;
1284 
1285  // Origin information
1286  Local<Value> resource_name;
1287  Local<Integer> resource_line_offset;
1288  Local<Integer> resource_column_offset;
1289  ScriptOriginOptions resource_options;
1290  Local<Value> source_map_url;
1291 
1292  // Cached data from previous compilation (if a kConsume*Cache flag is
1293  // set), or hold newly generated cache data (kProduce*Cache flags) are
1294  // set when calling a compile method.
1295  CachedData* cached_data;
1296  };

3039 class V8_EXPORT Object : public Value {

3049  Local<Value> value);
3050 
3051  // Implements CreateDataProperty (ECMA-262, 7.3.4).
3052  //
3053  // Defines a configurable, writable, enumerable property with the given value
3054  // on the object unless the property already exists and is not configurable
3055  // or the object is not extensible.
3056  //
3057  // Returns true on success.
3058  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT Maybe<bool> CreateDataProperty(Local<Context> context,
3059  Local<Name> key,
3060  Local<Value> value);
3061  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT Maybe<bool> CreateDataProperty(Local<Context> context,
3062  uint32_t index,
3063  Local<Value> value);
3064 
3065  // Implements DefineOwnProperty.
3066  //
3067  // In general, CreateDataProperty will be faster, however, does not allow
3068  // for specifying attributes.
3069  //
3070  // Returns true on success.
3071  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT Maybe<bool> DefineOwnProperty(
3072  Local<Context> context, Local<Name> key, Local<Value> value,
3073  PropertyAttribute attributes = None);
3074 
3075  // Implements Object.DefineProperty(O, P, Attributes), see Ecma-262 19.1.2.4.
3076  //
3077  // The defineProperty function is used to add an own property or
3078  // update the attributes of an existing own property of an object.
3079  //
3080  // Both data and accessor descriptors can be used.
3081  //
3082  // In general, CreateDataProperty is faster, however, does not allow
3083  // for specifying attributes or an accessor descriptor.
3084  //
3085  // The PropertyDescriptor can change when redefining a property.
3086  //
3087  // Returns true on success.
3088  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT Maybe<bool> DefineProperty(
3089  Local<Context> context, Local<Name> key, PropertyDescriptor& descriptor);
3090 
3091  // Sets an own property on this object bypassing interceptors and
3092  // overriding accessors or read-only properties.
3093  //
3094  // Note that if the object has an interceptor the property will be set
3095  // locally, but since the interceptor takes precedence the local property
3096  // will only be returned if the interceptor doesn't return a value.
3097  //
3098  // Note also that this only works for named properties.
3099  V8_DEPRECATED("Use CreateDataProperty / DefineOwnProperty",
3100  Maybe<bool> ForceSet(Local<Context> context, Local<Value> key,
3101  Local<Value> value,
3102  PropertyAttribute attribs = None));
3103

3583 template<typename T>
3584 class ReturnValue {
3585  public:
3586  template <class S> V8_INLINE ReturnValue(const ReturnValue<S>& that)
3587  : value_(that.value_) {
3588  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
3589  }
3590  // Local setters
3591  template <typename S>
3592  V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("Use Global<> instead",
3593  void Set(const Persistent<S>& handle));
3594  template <typename S>
3595  V8_INLINE void Set(const Global<S>& handle);
3596  template <typename S>
3597  V8_INLINE void Set(const Local<S> handle);
3598  // Fast primitive setters
3599  V8_INLINE void Set(bool value);
3600  V8_INLINE void Set(double i);
3601  V8_INLINE void Set(int32_t i);
3602  V8_INLINE void Set(uint32_t i);
3603  // Fast JS primitive setters
3604  V8_INLINE void SetNull();
3605  V8_INLINE void SetUndefined();
3606  V8_INLINE void SetEmptyString();
3607  // Convenience getter for Isolate
3608  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const;
3609 
3610  // Pointer setter: Uncompilable to prevent inadvertent misuse.
3611  template <typename S>
3612  V8_INLINE void Set(S* whatever);
3613 
3614  // Getter. Creates a new Local<> so it comes with a certain performance
3615  // hit. If the ReturnValue was not yet set, this will return the undefined
3616  // value.
3617  V8_INLINE Local<Value> Get() const;
3618 
3619  private:
3620  template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
3621  template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
3622  template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
3623  template <class F, class G, class H>
3624  friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
3625  V8_INLINE void SetInternal(internal::Object* value) { *value_ = value; }
3626  V8_INLINE internal::Object* GetDefaultValue();
3627  V8_INLINE explicit ReturnValue(internal::Object** slot);
3628  internal::Object** value_;
3629 };

4095 // TODO(mtrofin): rename WasmCompiledModule to WasmModuleObject, for
4096 // consistency with internal APIs.
4097 class V8_EXPORT WasmCompiledModule : public Object {
4098  public:
4099  typedef std::pair<std::unique_ptr<const uint8_t[]>, size_t> SerializedModule;
4100  // A buffer that is owned by the caller.
4101  typedef std::pair<const uint8_t*, size_t> CallerOwnedBuffer;
4102 
4103  // An opaque, native heap object for transferring wasm modules. It
4104  // supports move semantics, and does not support copy semantics.
4105  class TransferrableModule final {
4106  public:
4107  TransferrableModule(TransferrableModule&& src) = default;
4108  TransferrableModule(const TransferrableModule& src) = delete;
4109 
4110  TransferrableModule& operator=(TransferrableModule&& src) = default;
4111  TransferrableModule& operator=(const TransferrableModule& src) = delete;
4112 
4113  private:
4114  typedef std::pair<std::unique_ptr<const uint8_t[]>, size_t> OwnedBuffer;
4115  friend class WasmCompiledModule;
4116  TransferrableModule(OwnedBuffer&& code, OwnedBuffer&& bytes)
4117  : compiled_code(std::move(code)), wire_bytes(std::move(bytes)) {}
4118 
4119  OwnedBuffer compiled_code = {nullptr, 0};
4120  OwnedBuffer wire_bytes = {nullptr, 0};
4121  };
4122 
4123  // Get an in-memory, non-persistable, and context-independent (meaning,
4124  // suitable for transfer to another Isolate and Context) representation
4125  // of this wasm compiled module.
4126  TransferrableModule GetTransferrableModule();
4127 
4128  // Efficiently re-create a WasmCompiledModule, without recompiling, from
4129  // a TransferrableModule.
4130  static MaybeLocal<WasmCompiledModule> FromTransferrableModule(
4131  Isolate* isolate, const TransferrableModule&);
4132 
4133  // Get the wasm-encoded bytes that were used to compile this module.
4134  Local<String> GetWasmWireBytes();
4135 
4136  // Serialize the compiled module. The serialized data does not include the
4137  // uncompiled bytes.
4138  SerializedModule Serialize();
4139 
4140  // If possible, deserialize the module, otherwise compile it from the provided
4141  // uncompiled bytes.
4142  static MaybeLocal<WasmCompiledModule> DeserializeOrCompile(
4143  Isolate* isolate, const CallerOwnedBuffer& serialized_module,
4144  const CallerOwnedBuffer& wire_bytes);
4145  V8_INLINE static WasmCompiledModule* Cast(Value* obj);
4146 
4147  private:
4148  // TODO(ahaas): please remove the friend once streamed compilation is
4149  // implemented
4150  friend class WasmModuleObjectBuilder;
4151 
4152  static MaybeLocal<WasmCompiledModule> Deserialize(
4153  Isolate* isolate, const CallerOwnedBuffer& serialized_module,
4154  const CallerOwnedBuffer& wire_bytes);
4155  static MaybeLocal<WasmCompiledModule> Compile(Isolate* isolate,
4156  const uint8_t* start,
4157  size_t length);
4158  static CallerOwnedBuffer AsCallerOwned(
4159  const TransferrableModule::OwnedBuffer& buff) {
4160  return {buff.first.get(), buff.second};
4161  }
4162 
4163  WasmCompiledModule();
4164  static void CheckCast(Value* obj);
4165 };

6461 struct JitCodeEvent {
6462  enum EventType {
6463  CODE_ADDED,
6464  CODE_MOVED,
6465  CODE_REMOVED,
6466  CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
6467  CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
6468  CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
6469  };
6470  // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
6471  // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
6472  // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
6473  // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
6474  // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
6475  enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
6476 
6477  // Type of event.
6478  EventType type;
6479  // Start of the instructions.
6480  void* code_start;
6481  // Size of the instructions.
6482  size_t code_len;
6483  // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
6484  Local<UnboundScript> script;
6485  // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
6486  // code line information which is returned from the
6487  // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
6488  // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
6489  void* user_data;
6490 
6491  struct name_t {
6492  // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
6493  // zero-terminated.
6494  const char* str;
6495  // Number of chars in str.
6496  size_t len;
6497  };
6498 
6499  struct line_info_t {
6500  // PC offset
6501  size_t offset;
6502  // Code postion
6503  size_t pos;
6504  // The position type.
6505  PositionType position_type;
6506  };
6507 
6508  union {
6509  // Only valid for CODE_ADDED.
6510  struct name_t name;
6511 
6512  // Only valid for CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO
6513  struct line_info_t line_info;
6514 
6515  // New location of instructions. Only valid for CODE_MOVED.
6516  void* new_code_start;
6517  };
6518 };
6519 
6525 enum RAILMode {
6526  // Response performance mode: In this mode very low virtual machine latency
6527  // is provided. V8 will try to avoid JavaScript execution interruptions.
6528  // Throughput may be throttled.
6529  PERFORMANCE_RESPONSE,
6530  // Animation performance mode: In this mode low virtual machine latency is
6531  // provided. V8 will try to avoid as many JavaScript execution interruptions
6532  // as possible. Throughput may be throttled. This is the default mode.
6533  PERFORMANCE_ANIMATION,
6534  // Idle performance mode: The embedder is idle. V8 can complete deferred work
6535  // in this mode.
6536  PERFORMANCE_IDLE,
6537  // Load performance mode: In this mode high throughput is provided. V8 may
6538  // turn off latency optimizations.
6539  PERFORMANCE_LOAD
6540 };
6541

8189 
8200 template <class T>
8201 class Maybe {
8202  public:
8203  V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value_; }
8204  V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value_; }
8205 
8209  V8_INLINE T ToChecked() const { return FromJust(); }
8210 
8215  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool To(T* out) const {
8216  if (V8_LIKELY(IsJust())) *out = value_;
8217  return IsJust();
8218  }
8219 
8224  V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
8225  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
8226  return value_;
8227  }
8228 
8233  V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
8234  return has_value_ ? value_ : default_value;
8235  }
8236 
8237  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
8238  return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
8239  (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
8240  }
8241 
8242  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
8243  return !operator==(other);
8244  }
8245 
8246  private:
8247  Maybe() : has_value_(false) {}
8248  explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value_(true), value_(t) {}
8249 
8250  bool has_value_;
8251  T value_;
8252 
8253  template <class U>
8254  friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
8255  template <class U>
8256  friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
8257 };
8258 
8259 
8260 template <class T>
8261 inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
8262  return Maybe<T>();
8263 }
8264 
8265 
8266 template <class T>
8267 inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
8268  return Maybe<T>(t);
8269 }

8832 
8833 const int kApiPointerSize = sizeof(void*); // NOLINT
8834 const int kApiIntSize = sizeof(int); // NOLINT
8835 const int kApiInt64Size = sizeof(int64_t); // NOLINT
8836 
8837 // Tag information for HeapObject.
8838 const int kHeapObjectTag = 1;
8839 const int kHeapObjectTagSize = 2;
8840 const intptr_t kHeapObjectTagMask = (1 << kHeapObjectTagSize) - 1;
8841 
8842 // Tag information for Smi.
8843 const int kSmiTag = 0;
8844 const int kSmiTagSize = 1;
8845 const intptr_t kSmiTagMask = (1 << kSmiTagSize) - 1;
8846 
8847 template <size_t ptr_size> struct SmiTagging;
8848 
8849 template<int kSmiShiftSize>
8850 V8_INLINE internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
8851  int smi_shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
8852  uintptr_t tagged_value =
8853  (static_cast<uintptr_t>(value) << smi_shift_bits) | kSmiTag;
8854  return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object*>(tagged_value);
8855 }
8856 
8857 // Smi constants for 32-bit systems.
8858 template <> struct SmiTagging<4> {
8859  enum { kSmiShiftSize = 0, kSmiValueSize = 31 };
8860  static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
8861  static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
8862  V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
8863  int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
8864  // Throw away top 32 bits and shift down (requires >> to be sign extending).
8865  return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value)) >> shift_bits;
8866  }
8867  V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
8868  return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
8869  }
8870  V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
8871  // To be representable as an tagged small integer, the two
8872  // most-significant bits of 'value' must be either 00 or 11 due to
8873  // sign-extension. To check this we add 01 to the two
8874  // most-significant bits, and check if the most-significant bit is 0
8875  //
8876  // CAUTION: The original code below:
8877  // bool result = ((value + 0x40000000) & 0x80000000) == 0;
8878  // may lead to incorrect results according to the C language spec, and
8879  // in fact doesn't work correctly with gcc4.1.1 in some cases: The
8880  // compiler may produce undefined results in case of signed integer
8881  // overflow. The computation must be done w/ unsigned ints.
8882  return static_cast<uintptr_t>(value + 0x40000000U) < 0x80000000U;
8883  }
8884 };
8885 
8886 // Smi constants for 64-bit systems.
8887 template <> struct SmiTagging<8> {
8888  enum { kSmiShiftSize = 31, kSmiValueSize = 32 };
8889  static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
8890  static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
8891  V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
8892  int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
8893  // Shift down and throw away top 32 bits.
8894  return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) >> shift_bits);
8895  }
8896  V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
8897  return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
8898  }
8899  V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
8900  // To be representable as a long smi, the value must be a 32-bit integer.
8901  return (value == static_cast<int32_t>(value));
8902  }
8903 };
8904 
8905 typedef SmiTagging<kApiPointerSize> PlatformSmiTagging;
8906 const int kSmiShiftSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiShiftSize;
8907 const int kSmiValueSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiValueSize;
8908 V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre31Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 31; }
8909 V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre32Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 32; }

8934  static const int kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag = 0x0a;

8938  static const int kExternalMemoryLimitOffset =
8939  kExternalMemoryOffset + kApiInt64Size;

8954  static const int kNodeStateMask = 0x7;
8955  static const int kNodeStateIsWeakValue = 2;
8956  static const int kNodeStateIsPendingValue = 3;
8957  static const int kNodeStateIsNearDeathValue = 4;

8959  static const int kNodeIsActiveShift = 4;

8979  V8_INLINE static bool HasHeapObjectTag(const internal::Object* value) {

8981  kHeapObjectTag);
8982  }

8985  return PlatformSmiTagging::SmiToInt(value);

8996  V8_INLINE static int GetInstanceType(const internal::Object* obj) {
8997  typedef internal::Object O;
8998  O* map = ReadField<O*>(obj, kHeapObjectMapOffset);
8999  // Map::InstanceType is defined so that it will always be loaded into
9000  // the LS 8 bits of one 16-bit word, regardless of endianess.
9001  return ReadField<uint16_t>(map, kMapInstanceTypeAndBitFieldOffset) & 0xff;
9002  }
9003 
9004  V8_INLINE static int GetOddballKind(const internal::Object* obj) {
9005  typedef internal::Object O;
9006  return SmiValue(ReadField<O*>(obj, kOddballKindOffset));
9007  }
9008 
9009  V8_INLINE static bool IsExternalTwoByteString(int instance_type) {
9010  int representation = (instance_type & kFullStringRepresentationMask);
9011  return representation == kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag;
9012  }
9013 
9014  V8_INLINE static uint8_t GetNodeFlag(internal::Object** obj, int shift) {
9015  uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
9016  return *addr & static_cast<uint8_t>(1U << shift);
9017  }
9018 
9019  V8_INLINE static void UpdateNodeFlag(internal::Object** obj,
9020  bool value, int shift) {
9021  uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
9022  uint8_t mask = static_cast<uint8_t>(1U << shift);
9023  *addr = static_cast<uint8_t>((*addr & ~mask) | (value << shift));
9024  }
9025 
9026  V8_INLINE static uint8_t GetNodeState(internal::Object** obj) {
9027  uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
9028  return *addr & kNodeStateMask;
9029  }
9030 
9031  V8_INLINE static void UpdateNodeState(internal::Object** obj,
9032  uint8_t value) {
9033  uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
9034  *addr = static_cast<uint8_t>((*addr & ~kNodeStateMask) | value);
9035  }
9036 
9037  V8_INLINE static void SetEmbedderData(v8::Isolate* isolate,
9038  uint32_t slot,
9039  void* data) {
9040  uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(isolate) +
9041  kIsolateEmbedderDataOffset + slot * kApiPointerSize;
9042  *reinterpret_cast<void**>(addr) = data;
9043  }
9044 
9045  V8_INLINE static void* GetEmbedderData(const v8::Isolate* isolate,
9046  uint32_t slot) {
9047  const uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(isolate) +
9048  kIsolateEmbedderDataOffset + slot * kApiPointerSize;
9049  return *reinterpret_cast<void* const*>(addr);
9050  }
9051 
9052  V8_INLINE static internal::Object** GetRoot(v8::Isolate* isolate,
9053  int index) {
9054  uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(isolate) + kIsolateRootsOffset;
9055  return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(addr + index * kApiPointerSize);
9056  }
9057 
9058  template <typename T>
9059  V8_INLINE static T ReadField(const internal::Object* ptr, int offset) {
9060  const uint8_t* addr =
9061  reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(ptr) + offset - kHeapObjectTag;
9062  return *reinterpret_cast<const T*>(addr);
9063  }
9064 
9065  template <typename T>
9066  V8_INLINE static T ReadEmbedderData(const v8::Context* context, int index) {
9067  typedef internal::Object O;
9068  typedef internal::Internals I;
9069  O* ctx = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(context);
9070  int embedder_data_offset = I::kContextHeaderSize +
9071  (internal::kApiPointerSize * I::kContextEmbedderDataIndex);
9072  O* embedder_data = I::ReadField<O*>(ctx, embedder_data_offset);
9073  int value_offset =
9074  I::kFixedArrayHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
9075  return I::ReadField<T>(embedder_data, value_offset);
9076  }
9077 };

9154  this->val_ = reinterpret_cast<T*>(V8::CopyPersistent(p));
9155  M::Copy(that, this);
9156 }

9164  I::kNodeIsIndependentShift);

9168 template <class T>

9170  typedef internal::Internals I;
9171  if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
9172  uint8_t node_state =
9173  I::GetNodeState(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_));
9174  return node_state == I::kNodeStateIsNearDeathValue ||
9175  node_state == I::kNodeStateIsPendingValue;
9176 }

9321 template<typename T>
9322 void ReturnValue<T>::Set(double i) {
9323  TYPE_CHECK(T, Number);
9324  Set(Number::New(GetIsolate(), i));
9325 }
9326 
9327 template<typename T>
9328 void ReturnValue<T>::Set(int32_t i) {
9329  TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
9330  typedef internal::Internals I;
9331  if (V8_LIKELY(I::IsValidSmi(i))) {
9332  *value_ = I::IntToSmi(i);
9333  return;
9334  }
9335  Set(Integer::New(GetIsolate(), i));
9336 }
9337 
9338 template<typename T>
9339 void ReturnValue<T>::Set(uint32_t i) {
9340  TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
9341  // Can't simply use INT32_MAX here for whatever reason.
9342  bool fits_into_int32_t = (i & (1U << 31)) == 0;
9343  if (V8_LIKELY(fits_into_int32_t)) {
9344  Set(static_cast<int32_t>(i));
9345  return;
9346  }
9347  Set(Integer::NewFromUnsigned(GetIsolate(), i));
9348 }
9349 
9350 template<typename T>
9351 void ReturnValue<T>::Set(bool value) {
9352  TYPE_CHECK(T, Boolean);
9353  typedef internal::Internals I;
9354  int root_index;
9355  if (value) {
9356  root_index = I::kTrueValueRootIndex;
9357  } else {
9358  root_index = I::kFalseValueRootIndex;
9359  }
9360  *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), root_index);
9361 }
9362 
9363 template<typename T>
9364 void ReturnValue<T>::SetNull() {
9365  TYPE_CHECK(T, Primitive);
9366  typedef internal::Internals I;
9367  *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kNullValueRootIndex);
9368 }

9373  typedef internal::Internals I;
9374  *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kUndefinedValueRootIndex);
9375 }

9384 template <typename T>

9386  // Isolate is always the pointer below the default value on the stack.
9387  return *reinterpret_cast<Isolate**>(&value_[-2]);
9388 }

9390 template <typename T>
9391 Local<Value> ReturnValue<T>::Get() const {
9392  typedef internal::Internals I;
9393  if (*value_ == *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kTheHoleValueRootIndex))
9394  return Local<Value>(*Undefined(GetIsolate()));
9395  return Local<Value>::New(GetIsolate(), reinterpret_cast<Value*>(value_));
9396 }

9402  TYPE_CHECK(S*, Primitive);
9403 }

9405 template<typename T>
9406 internal::Object* ReturnValue<T>::GetDefaultValue() {

9408  return value_[-1];

9556 
9557 Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
9558 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9559  typedef internal::Object O;
9560  typedef internal::HeapObject HO;
9561  typedef internal::Internals I;
9562  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
9563  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
9564  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
9565  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
9566  if (instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
9567  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType) {
9568  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
9569  O* value = I::ReadField<O*>(obj, offset);
9570  O** result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(reinterpret_cast<HO*>(obj), value);
9571  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
9572  }
9573 #endif
9574  return SlowGetInternalField(index);
9575 }
9576 
9577 
9578 void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
9579 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9580  typedef internal::Object O;
9581  typedef internal::Internals I;
9582  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
9583  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
9584  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
9585  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
9586  if (V8_LIKELY(instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
9587  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType)) {
9588  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
9589  return I::ReadField<void*>(obj, offset);
9590  }
9591 #endif
9592  return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
9593 }

9603 Local<String> String::Empty(Isolate* isolate) {

9611 
9612 String::ExternalStringResource* String::GetExternalStringResource() const {
9613  typedef internal::Object O;
9614  typedef internal::Internals I;
9615  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9616  String::ExternalStringResource* result;
9617  if (I::IsExternalTwoByteString(I::GetInstanceType(obj))) {
9618  void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
9619  result = reinterpret_cast<String::ExternalStringResource*>(value);
9620  } else {
9621  result = NULL;
9622  }
9623 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9624  VerifyExternalStringResource(result);
9625 #endif
9626  return result;
9627 }
9628 
9629 
9630 String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBase(
9631  String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
9632  typedef internal::Object O;
9633  typedef internal::Internals I;
9634  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9635  int type = I::GetInstanceType(obj) & I::kFullStringRepresentationMask;
9636  *encoding_out = static_cast<Encoding>(type & I::kStringEncodingMask);
9637  ExternalStringResourceBase* resource = NULL;
9638  if (type == I::kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag ||
9639  type == I::kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag) {
9640  void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
9641  resource = static_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);
9642  }
9643 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9644  VerifyExternalStringResourceBase(resource, *encoding_out);
9645 #endif
9646  return resource;
9647 }

9658 bool Value::QuickIsUndefined() const {
9659  typedef internal::Object O;
9660  typedef internal::Internals I;
9661  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9662  if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
9663  if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
9664  return (I::GetOddballKind(obj) == I::kUndefinedOddballKind);
9665 }

9693 bool Value::QuickIsNullOrUndefined() const {
9694  typedef internal::Object O;
9695  typedef internal::Internals I;
9696  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9697  if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
9698  if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
9699  int kind = I::GetOddballKind(obj);
9700  return kind == I::kNullOddballKind || kind == I::kUndefinedOddballKind;
9701 }

10156 
10157 int64_t Isolate::AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemory(
10158  int64_t change_in_bytes) {
10159  typedef internal::Internals I;
10160  const int64_t kMemoryReducerActivationLimit = 32 * 1024 * 1024;
10161  int64_t* external_memory = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
10162  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryOffset);
10163  int64_t* external_memory_limit = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
10164  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryLimitOffset);
10165  int64_t* external_memory_at_last_mc =
10166  reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
10167  I::kExternalMemoryAtLastMarkCompactOffset);
10168  const int64_t amount = *external_memory + change_in_bytes;
10169 
10170  *external_memory = amount;
10171 
10172  int64_t allocation_diff_since_last_mc =
10173  *external_memory_at_last_mc - *external_memory;
10174  allocation_diff_since_last_mc = allocation_diff_since_last_mc < 0
10175  ? -allocation_diff_since_last_mc
10176  : allocation_diff_since_last_mc;
10177  if (allocation_diff_since_last_mc > kMemoryReducerActivationLimit) {
10178  CheckMemoryPressure();
10179  }
10180 
10181  if (change_in_bytes < 0) {
10182  *external_memory_limit += change_in_bytes;
10183  }
10184 
10185  if (change_in_bytes > 0 && amount > *external_memory_limit) {
10186  ReportExternalAllocationLimitReached();
10187  }
10188  return *external_memory;
10189 }

10191 Local<Value> Context::GetEmbedderData(int index) {
10192 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10193  typedef internal::Object O;
10194  typedef internal::HeapObject HO;
10195  typedef internal::Internals I;
10196  HO* context = *reinterpret_cast<HO**>(this);
10197  O** result =
10198  HandleScope::CreateHandle(context, I::ReadEmbedderData<O*>(this, index));
10199  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
10200 #else
10201  return SlowGetEmbedderData(index);
10202 #endif
10203 }
